cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.Medical Imaging, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to the problem of pulmonary nodule detection, which is a subfield of medical imaging. Therefore, "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and "cs.Medical Imaging" are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach to improve the sample complexity of CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses group convolutions, which is a technique from neural engineering, and hence "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as well.
